instances.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Python 3.7 or later\n- Django 3.2 or later\n\n## Features\n\n- Roll back to any point in a model instance's history.\n- Recover deleted model instances.\n- Simple admin integration.\n\n## Documentation\n\nCheck out the latest `django-reversion` documentation at [Getting Started](http://django-reversion.readthedocs.io/)\n\nIssue tracking and source code can be found at the\n[main project website](http://github.com/etianen/django-reversion).\n\nYou can keep up to date with the latest announcements by joining the\n[django-reversion discussion group](http://groups.google.com/group/django-reversion).\n\n## Upgrading\n\nPlease check the [Changelog](https://github.com/etianen/django-reversion/blob/master/CHANGELOG.rst) before upgrading\nyour installation of django-reversion.\n\n## Contributing\n\nBug reports, bug fixes, and new features are always welcome. Please raise issues on the\n[django-reversion project site](http://github.com/etianen/django-reversion), and submit\npull requests for any new code.\n\n1. Fork the [repository](http://github.com/etianen/django-reversion) on GitHub.\n2. Make a branch off of master and commit your changes to it.\n3. Install requirements.\n\n```bash\n$ pip install django psycopg2 mysqlclient -e .\n```\n\n4. Run the tests\n\n```bash\n$ tests/manage.py test tests\n```\n\n5. Create a Pull Request with your contribution\n\n## Contributors\n\nThe django-reversion project was developed by [Dave Hall](http://www.etianen.com/) and contributed\nto by [many other people](https://github.com/etianen/django-reversion/graphs/contributors).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "reversion.errors", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "reversion.errors.RevertError", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Exception thrown when something goes wrong with reverting a model."]}, {"name": "reversion.errors.Revisio